# ==============================================================================
# .python-version - Python Version Manager Configuration Template
# ==============================================================================
#
# LOCATION: /.python-version (project root)
#
# PURPOSE:
#   Specify the exact Python version required for this project. Tools like
#   pyenv, poetry, asdf, and mise read this file to automatically switch
#   to the correct Python interpreter.
#
# USAGE:
#   1. Copy this file to .python-version in your project root
#   2. Tools will auto-switch when entering the directory
#   3. CI/CD can use actions/setup-python with python-version-file
#
# BOOTSTRAP INTEGRATION:
#   Bootstrap scripts populate this from bootstrap.conf:
#   - PYTHON_VERSION -> The version number below
#   After setup, this file is the authoritative source for Python version.
#
# ==============================================================================

# Python version (major.minor.patch)
3.11.8

# Alternative formats supported by some tools:
# 3.11        (latest patch of 3.11)
# 3.11.8:.venv (version with venv path hint)
